<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     01-16 0444</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0454</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rain Dampens Carolinas; Rain and Snow in Northwest</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Rain dampened eastern parts of the Carolinas and light rain and
snow brushed the Pacific Northwest, but the rest of the country
stayed dry early today.
   Blizzard conditions forced the closure of a 45-mile stretch of
Interstate 84 between La Grande and Baker Sunday afternoon,
stranding hundreds of motorists in the storm-ravaged northeastern
Oregon. The road wasn't expected to reopen before this morning,
State Trooper Stan Terry said.
   Clouds and some fog stretched from eastern Texas to the Atlantic
Coast. Clouds also extended from the central and northern Pacific
Coast across to the Dakotas and the Great Lakes, while clear skies
predominated from Southern California to New Mexico, Colorado and
the central Mississippi Valley.
   Strong winds buffeted the eastern slopes of the Rockies in
Montana and Wyoming, with gusts up to 70 mph recorded in Casper,
Wyo., Sunday evening.
   Today's forecast called for scattered snowshowers from northern
Vermont and New York state across the upper Great Lakes to northern
parts of Minnesota and North Dakota, and in western Montana. Rain
was expected to be widespread in the Pacific Northwest. Fair skies
were forecast for the rest of the nation.
   Highs were expected to be in the 40s or 50s across much of the
nation. Highs were forecast to be in the teens in northeast Nevada;
in the 20s and 30s in much of the Plateau region, from southwest
Wyoming to western Colorado, and from the northern Plains through
the Great Lakes and upper Ohio Valley into New England; in the 60s
from southern California to the desert Southwest, and from northern
Florida to coastal South Carolina, and in the 70s and 80s in the
rest of Florida.
   At 2 a.m. EST, temperatures ranged from 15 degrees below zero at
Hibbing, Minn., to 72 degrees at Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 41 cloudy; Boston 35 fair; Buffalo 33 freezing
rain; Charleston, S.C. 62 foggy; Cincinnati 33 cloudy; Cleveland 33
cloudy; Detroit 30 foggy; Miami 68 fair; New York 38 fair;
Philadelphia 37 cloudy; Pittsburgh 32 cloudy; Portland, Maine 34
partly cloudy; Washington 40 rain.
   _Central: Bismarck 22 cloudy; Chicago 27 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
38 partly cloudy; Denver 18 fair; Des Moines 23 fair; Indianapolis
30 fair; Kansas City 27 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 8 fair; Nashville
36 foggy; New Orleans 49 fair; St. Louis 30 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 24 fair; Anchorage -9 partly cloudy; Las Vegas
30 fair; Los Angeles 55 fair; Phoenix 42 fair; Salt Lake City 12
fair; San Diego 46 fair; San Francisco 43 fair; Seattle 46 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 23 fair; Toronto 28 snow.
</TEXT>
