<FIRST>r a PM-PalsyTelethon     01-16 0123</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Palsy Telethon,0126</SECOND>
<HEAD>Cerebral Palsy Telethon Raises $22.6 Million in Pledges</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A nationwide weekend telethon raised nearly
$22.6 million in pledges to fight cerebral palsy, a crippling
disease that affects 700,000 Americans.
   The 21-hour Weekend With The Stars Telethon, with ``Hooperman''
star John Ritter as host, was broadcast on 80 television stations
around the country on Saturday and Sunday.
   The 11th annual telethon raised money for United Cerebral Palsy
Associations Inc., to conduct research and provide programs and
community services.
   The show raised $22,563,721 in pledges, including $737,048 from
the Los Angeles area, according to telethon officials.
   Among others appearing were Robert Urich and Joanna Kerns, Pia
Zadora, Dennis James, Florence Henderson and Ritter's wife, Nancy
Morgan Ritter.
</TEXT>
