<FIRST>r i PM-Ireland-Shooting     01-16 0168</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Ireland-Shooting,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gunmen Shoot Former Policeman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUBLIN, Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two gunmen killed a former reserve
policeman with Northern Ireland's Royal Ulster Constabulary in front
of his girlfriend, police said today.
   Harry Keyes, 25, was shot Sunday evening as he was backing out of
the driveway of his girlfriend's house in Ballintra in western
Ireland, eight miles from the border with Northern Ireland, police
said.
   Police did not name Keyes' friend, but said she was not hurt.
   There was no immediate claim of responsibility for the shooting.
But suspicion fell on the outlawed Irish Republican Army, which
targets police and army personnel in its fight to oust the British
from Northern Ireland.
   Also Sunday, Irish police uncovered a cache of arms and
ammunition hidden in a 40-gallon plastic drum beside a river near
Kilkenny, 70 miles south of Dublin, the spokesman said. Soviet-made
rifles, magazines and 1,400 rounds of ammunition were seized.
   A man is being held for questioning in connection with the arms,
the spokesman said.
</TEXT>
