<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--KKKParade     01-16 0142</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--KKK Parade,0145</SECOND>
<HEAD>Klan Has 1-Car Parade in Mount Dora</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOUNT DORA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Members of the Ku Klux Klan were shut out
of two Christmas parades, but they finally held their parade in this
central Florida town _ on the birthday of the Rev. Martin Luther
King Jr.
   The one-car procession Sunday featured four Klansmen in a car
draped with Confederate flags and a sign reading, ``Martin Luther
King was a commi.''
   The Klan members, two of whom wore white robes, stopped at City
Hall and read a statement proclaiming white supremacy.
   About 55 police officers and 150 spectators quietly watched the
proceedings.
   The Klan announced last month that it would march in Mount Dora's
annual Christmas parade, but authorities canceled the event. Later,
the Klan was excluded from a rescheduled parade when organizers made
it ``by invitation only.''
</TEXT>
