<SECOND>AM-BRF--Bones Found,0188</SECOND>
<HEAD>Desert Near El Paso Yields Third Body in a Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EL PASO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three bodies were found in the desert near
Interstate 10 in the last week, but police say the deaths appear to
be unrelated.
   A transient looking for a place to rest Sunday discovered a human
skeleton in a drainage tunnel under I-10 near the town of Fabens,
police said.
   Last weekend, the skeletal remains of 17-year-old Angela Irsay
were found near I-10 in east El Paso. And on Thursday, a passerby
found the body of a woman about five miles west of Fabens and 25
yards south of I-10. She had been bound and shot in the head, and a
cloth was put over her head and set afire.
   No arrests have been made.
   The last two victims have not been identified, and police do not
yet know the sex or cause of death of the body found Sunday,
Sheriff's Detective Marvin Ryals said.
   Miss Irsay had last been seen Sept. 22, according to police. The
cause of her death could not be determined.
