<FIRST>r f PM-AutoShow-Attendance     01-16 0141</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Auto Show-Attendance,0146</SECOND>
<HEAD>Revamped Detroit Auto Show Sets Attendance Record</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The revamped annual automotive show in the
nation's car making capital shattered previous attendance records by
drawing 636,722 people during its nine-day run, a show official said
today.
   Patrick Fitzgerald, spokesman for the North American
International Auto Show, said attendance at the Jan. 7-15 event
broke the 1986 record of 471,977. Last year's show, called the
Detroit Auto Show, drew 451,626 people.
   There were 41 exhibitors at this year's show, 17 more than last
year's, displaying nearly 700 cars and light trucks.
   For years, the Chicago Auto Show has stolen the thunder from the
Detroit show, and organizers said this year's show in Detroit would
put the city back on top of the U.S. auto show heap. The 1989
Chicago Auto Show is scheduled for Feb. 11-19.
</TEXT>
