<FIRST>u f PM-Shamrock-SoundWarehouse     01-16 0212</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Shamrock-Sound Warehouse,0219</SECOND>
<HEAD>Shamrock Holdings to Acqire Sound Warehouse</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Shamrock Holdings Inc. and Sound Warehouse Inc.,
one of the nation's leading retailers of home entertainment
software, have signed an agreement under which Shamrock will buy
Sound Warehouse for approximately $132.5 million, the companies said
today.
   Under the agreement, Shamrock's newly formed entertainment
subsidiary, Shamrock Entertainment II Inc., will merge into Sound
Warehouse and all stockholders of Sound Warehouse will receive
$25.65 in cash per share of common stock.
   Sound Warehouse plans to pay a cash dividend of up to 10 cents a
share to stockholders of record immediately before the merger, the
company said.
   The merger is subject to approval by stockholders of Sound
Warehouse at a meeting in March or early April.
   Sound Warehouse, based in Dallas, has 121 outlets in 13 states.
An additional 10 outlets are planned for opening by Dec. 31. For the
year ended May 31, Sound Warehouse had sales of $181 million and net
income of $4.2 million or 80 cents a share.
   Shamrock Holdings, based in Burbank, Calif., is wholly owned by
the Roy E. Disney family. In July 1988, the company purchased
privately held Show Industries Inc., a Los Angeles-area retailer of
home entertainment software through its subsidiary, Music Plus.
</TEXT>
