<FILEID>AP-NR-01-16-89 1541EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Computer     01-16 0182</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Computer,0188</SECOND>
<HEAD>NCR Earnings Fall, But Per-Share Earnings Set Record</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   NCR Corp. said its earnings fell 7.4 percent and revenue fell 1
percent in the fourth quarter, but the computer maker's stock
repurchase program lowered the number of outstanding shares and
helped it post record earnings per share for the period.
   NCR, of Dayton, Ohio, said it earned $149.6 million on revenue of
$1.80 billion in the three months ended Dec. 31, down from $161.4
million on revenue of $1.82 billion a year earlier. But a reduction
in outstanding shares caused earnings per share to rise to a record
$1.85 from $1.79 a year earlier.
   For the full year, NCR said its earnings rose 4.8 percent to
$439.3 million, or $5.33 per share, from $419.3 million, or $4.51 a
share. Revenue rose 6.2 percent to $5.99 billion from $5.64 billion.
   NCR said revenue outside the United States, which accounts for
more than half its total revenue, increased in the fourth quarter
and substantially offset declines in U.S. revenue. It said orders
set a record in the quarter.
</TEXT>
