<FIRST>r f AM-NorthernTelecom     01-16 0181</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Northern Telecom,0187</SECOND>
<HEAD>Northern Telecom Names Former Unisys Exec As CEO</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Northern Telecom Ltd., the Canadian
telecommunications company, said Monday it had picked former Unisys
Corp. executive Paul Stern to serve as its vice chairman and chief
executive.
   Stern, 50, will take the post on March 1 and then ascend to the
rank of chairman and chief executive at the time of the planned
retirement of Edmund B. Fitzgerald, the current chairman, in April
1990, the Mississauga, Ontario-based company said.
   Stern, a resident of Villanova, Pa., joined Northern Telecom's
board of directors and was elected to its executive committee in
April 1988 and has also served as a consultant to it since May.
   Stern joined Burroughs Corp. in 1981 as executive vice president
and was appointed president and chief operating officer in May 1982.
When Burroughs bought Sperry Corp. in 1986 to form Unisys, Stern
became president of the new company and served in that post until
Dec. 31, 1987.
   Northern Telecom, a leading supplier of digital phone equipment,
had 1987 revenue of about $4.9 billion.
</TEXT>
